column1: Consistent with a previous report [ 16], no obvious differences were found in the expression of " nutritive " genes ( Hnf4, Afp, Tfn, ApoAI, Apo - AIV, and ApoB) or genes involved in yolk sac hematopoiesis or vasculogenesis ( Ttr, Rbp, Flt1, Flk1, Tal1, Rbtn2, GATA1) ( data not shown), suggesting that huntingtin is not essential for the proper expression of genes required for the nutritive function of the extraembryonic tissues.
